data.content:
verb
-stretches; -stretched; -stretching
[+ obj] to stretch (something) too far or too much
Take care not to overstretch his sweater.
overstretch a muscle
chiefly Brit :to try to do too much with (something)
Don't overstretch your resources. :to try to make (someone) do too much
an overstretched serving staff
Home buyers should not financially overstretch themselves. [=not spend more money than they can afford to spend]
